SKATTO – MOBILE BREAKPOINT + ICON + TAB SPECIFICATION

This document defines how the mobile version must behave visually and structurally.
It also clarifies icon usage and tab/URL logic.

Visual reference (source of truth for layout and spacing):
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto%20Phone%20Example.png?raw=true

Footer image reference:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto%20phone%20footer.png?raw=true

⸻

1. BREAKPOINT

Mobile layout applies at:

max-width: 768px

Primary reference width:
390px (standard iPhone width)

Content container:
90–92% of viewport width
Max-width: 520px

White space must be preserved.
No compressed spacing.

⸻

2. HEADER (MOBILE)

Structure (stacked vertically):

• Small Skatto logo top left
• “BERÄKNA” button top right
• Large Skatto logo centered
• Slogan: SKATT, UTAN KRÅNGEL.
• Three checkmarks stacked vertically

Adjustments from desktop:

• Checkmarks stack vertically
• Generous vertical spacing between elements
• Button remains pill-shaped
• Logo scales proportionally

Hierarchy must remain identical to desktop, only layout changes.

⸻

3. TAB SYSTEM (MOBILE AND DESKTOP – SAME LOGIC)

Tabs must visually look like tabs, not buttons.

Each calculator has its own URL:

/enskildfirma
/anstallning
/kryptoskatt

Behavior:

• Clicking a tab changes the URL
• Loading a URL preselects the correct tab
• No tab switching without URL change

Visual behavior:

Active tab:
• Filled with gradient (same as calculator card)
• White icon
• White text
• No bottom border
• Visually merged into calculator card

Inactive tab:
• White background
• Thin border in gradient color
• Lavender icon
• Dark text

On mobile:
Tabs must be horizontally scrollable if needed.

Tab and URL logic must be identical across all breakpoints.

⸻

4. CALCULATOR CARD

Gradient background (all breakpoints):

Linear gradient:
#7E8EC6 → #6389C6

Border radius: 20px
Internal padding: 24px
Field spacing: 16–20px

Inputs:
• White background
• 12–14px border radius
• Subtle shadow
• Clear readable font

No heavy outlines.

⸻

5. ICON SYSTEM (ALL BREAKPOINTS)

Icons must be used consistently on:

• Tabs
• Text blocks
• Highlight sections
• Desktop and mobile

No black icons.
Only brand lavender or off-white versions.

⸻

Icon Assets

Anställning – Lavender:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Ansta%CC%88llning_Lavender.png?raw=true

Anställning – Off-white:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Ansta%CC%88llning_off%20white.png?raw=true

Enskild firma – Lavender:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Enskild%20firma_Lavender.png?raw=true

Enskild firma – Off-white:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Enskild%20firma_off%20white.png?raw=true

Krypto – Lavender:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Krypto_Lavender.png?raw=true

Krypto – Off-white:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto_Icons_Krypto_off%20white.png?raw=true

Usage rules:

• Active tab → Off-white icon
• Inactive tab → Lavender icon
• Text sections → Lavender
• On gradient backgrounds → Off-white

Icons must scale proportionally and maintain consistent visual weight.

Icons must also be used on the desktop breakpoint.

⸻

6. “SÅ RÄKNAR VI” SECTION

Current implementation is incorrect.

It must visually match this structure:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Sa%20raknar%20vi%20visual%20guideline.png?raw=true

Structure:

Section title:
Så räknar vi

Toggle link:
Visa hela beräkningen ▼

Collapsed state:
Show short summary only.

Expanded state:
Show grouped structured calculation blocks.

Typography:

Group headers:
• ALL CAPS
• Light weight
• Increased letter spacing
• Slightly larger than body text

Example structure:

ÖVERSKOTT
Vinst
Schablonavdrag
Överskott (bold)

BESKATTNINGSBAR INKOMST
Grundavdrag
Beskattningsbar inkomst (bold)

TOTAL SKATTEFORDRAN (bold)

Spacing:

Desktop: 40px between blocks
Mobile: 28px between blocks

Mobile layout:
Single column
Amounts right aligned
Subtle dividers only

No heavy borders.

Layout must feel structured, calm and readable.

⸻

7. FOOTER (GLOBAL COMPONENT)

Footer must be identical across all pages and breakpoints.

Implementation:
	1.	Render footer image full width:
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Skatto%20phone%20footer.png?raw=true
	2.	Below image render:

© Skatto 2026
Om Skatto
Kontakt
Integritetspolicy
Villkor
Cookies
	3.	Below menu add disclaimer text:

Skatto är ett beräkningsverktyg som ger uppskattningar baserat på gällande schabloner. Resultaten ersätter inte rådgivning från Skatteverket eller redovisningskonsult.

Footer must appear on all pages.

⸻

8. DESIGN PRINCIPLES

Mobile must feel:

• Calm
• Spacious
• Structured
• Not crowded

White space is intentional.
Hierarchy is more important than decoration.
No visual clutter.

Tab logic, icon logic and structure must remain consistent across desktop and mobile.

